docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — A federal judge on Monday rejected plea agreements with the Justice Department for two of the three white men facing hate crime charges in the killing of Ahmaud Arbery after his family expressed fierce opposition to the deal.

headline.main: Federal Judge Rejects Hate Crime Plea Deals in Ahmaud Arbery Killing
headline.print_headline: Judge Rejects Two Plea Deals In Arbery Case

docs.abstract: Progressive philanthropists who fund groups that promote extreme views are “exacerbating intraparty conflict and stoking interparty backlash.”
docs.snippet: Progressive philanthropists who fund groups that promote extreme views are “exacerbating intraparty conflict and stoking interparty backlash.”
docs.lead_paragraph: The killing of George Floyd and the nationwide Black Lives Matter protests that followed drove an exceptionally large increase in foundation grants and pledges to criminal and racial justice reform groups and other causes, ranging from the United Negro College Fund to the Center for Antiracist Research and from the National Museum of African American History to the Yes 4 Minneapolis campaign to dismantle the Minneapolis Police Department.

headline.main: The Law of Unintended Political Consequences Strikes Again

docs.abstract: Unlike the Derek Chauvin murder trial, whose jury was drawn only from the Minneapolis area, the federal trial of Mr. Chauvin’s colleagues included jurors from across Minnesota.
docs.snippet: Unlike the Derek Chauvin murder trial, whose jury was drawn only from the Minneapolis area, the federal trial of Mr. Chauvin’s colleagues included jurors from across Minnesota.
docs.lead_paragraph: ST. PAUL, Minn. — All 12 jurors who weighed federal charges against three officers who were at the scene of George Floyd’s death appear to be white, differing significantly from the racially diverse jury that convicted a fourth officer, Derek Chauvin of murdering Mr. Floyd.

headline.main: All of the jurors who decided the case appeared to be white.

docs.abstract: “I was thinking about Balanchine a lot,” said Roberts, Ailey’s choreographer in residence, who is making his first work for New York City Ballet.
docs.snippet: “I was thinking about Balanchine a lot,” said Roberts, Ailey’s choreographer in residence, who is making his first work for New York City Ballet.
docs.lead_paragraph: So much has happened since Jamar Roberts was to have had his choreographic debut at New York City Ballet, in May 2020. Before he had even set foot in the studio with the dancers, the pandemic shut everything down. Then came a national period of soul searching around the issue of race brought on by the killing of George Floyd.

headline.main: At City Ballet, Jamar Roberts and Dancers Find a Common Language

docs.abstract: One man will be eligible for parole after 30 years. The three face a federal trial on hate crime charges next month.
docs.snippet: One man will be eligible for parole after 30 years. The three face a federal trial on hate crime charges next month.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — A Georgia judge on Friday sentenced both Travis McMichael, the man who fatally shot Ahmaud Arbery, and his father to life in prison without the possibility of parole, but issued a lesser sentence of life with the possibility of parole to the other white man convicted of murdering Mr. Arbery, a 25-year-old Black man whom they had chased through their neighborhood.

headline.main: Three Men Sentenced to Life in Prison in Arbery Killing
headline.print_headline: Georgia Judge Sentences Three Men to Life in Prison in Arbery Killing
